				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mid {}_{{\left\{\overset{\sim }{x_i}\right\}}^{(j)}} $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M6" display="inline"><mml:mo>∣</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mrow/><mml:msup><mml:mfenced close="}" open="{"><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:msub><mml:mi>x</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo stretchy="true">~</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:mfenced><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:mfenced></mml:msup></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12864_2018_5350_Article_IEq1.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> indicates that the derivative has been evaluated at the root point <inline-formula id="IEq2"><alternatives><tex-math id="M7">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
